{"word":"ὄστρεον","slug":"ὄστρεον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n75653\" key=\"o)/streon\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὄστρε-ον</orth> or <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὄστρειον</orth>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">τό</gen>, <sense id=\"n75653.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">oyster</tr_>; the proper <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Att.\">Att.</a></gram> </gramGrp> form is <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὄστρειον </foreign>(<cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὄστρεια . . ἔλεγον οἱ ἀρχαῖοι</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0008.tlg001.perseus-grc1:3:92e\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ath.\">Ath.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.92e</biblScope></bibl></cit>, cf. Moer.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0008.tlg001.perseus-grc1:p.285\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">p.285</biblScope> </bibl> P. (who recommends <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὀστρία <pron extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pron\">[ῑ]</pron> </foreign> wrongly), <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Phot.</author></bibl>, etc.), and this is required by the metre in the earlier Poets, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">κόγχοι, μύες, κὤστρεια</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0085.tlg008:34\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ A.\">A.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Fr.\">Fr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">34</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quo